---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { site } from "../lib/site";
---

<BaseLayout title="ShipAudit privacy" description="Privacy practices for the ShipAudit validation site.">
  <section class="py-14 md:py-20">
    <div class="shell max-w-3xl prose-ship">
      <p class="eyebrow m-0">Privacy</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black">Privacy notice (validation phase)</h1>
      <p class="text-[var(--muted)]">Last updated: 12 July 2026 · Contact: {site.securityEmail}</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        ShipAudit is operated as a validation product under {site.productHost}. Customer and security contact:
        <a href={`mailto:${site.securityEmail}`}>{site.securityEmail}</a>. Infrastructure accounts may use
        {site.adminEmail} and are not a customer support channel.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Founding review forms:</strong> name, email, app URL, stack, optional launch date and free-text
          context. Drafts may be stored in your browser sessionStorage until you navigate away.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Email:</strong> messages you send to {site.securityEmail}.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Payments:</strong> processed by the merchant of record (Creem and/or Stripe when configured). We
          receive payment confirmation metadata needed to fulfill orders; card data is handled by the processor.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Waitlist:</strong> email and optional domain if you join the automatic-scan waitlist.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Hosting logs:</strong> standard CDN/request logs from Cloudflare or the static host (IP truncated or
          hashed where we control storage per future API design).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">What we do not want</h2>
      <p>
        Do not send passwords, session cookies, Authorization headers, production secrets or database credentials.
        If you send them by mistake, tell us immediately so we can delete them from mailboxes.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">How we use data</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Deliver Founding Expert Reviews and related support</li>
        <li>Record orders, refunds and SLA timelines</li>
        <li>Improve checklist quality using aggregated, non-secret lessons</li>
        <li>Contact waitlist subscribers when automation is ready (no guaranteed date)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Order and delivery records are kept as long as needed for accounting, dispute handling and product
        improvement. Waitlist emails can be removed on request. Future automated reports (not yet live) are planned
        for ~90-day default retention.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We share data with payment processors and hosting providers as required to operate the service. We do not
        sell personal data.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Your requests</h2>
      <p>
        Email {site.securityEmail} to access, correct or delete personal data we hold, subject to legal retention
        needs for paid orders.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
